{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567137","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567137"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:55:33+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:55:33+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18937"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18937","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18937"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.03,0.02,0.62,0.02,0.31]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11671"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107657"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11671","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11671"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18937"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90089"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5643"},{"type":"tags","id":"5750"},{"type":"tags","id":"5753"},{"type":"tags","id":"5770"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11282"},{"type":"tags","id":"11297"},{"type":"tags","id":"11304"},{"type":"tags","id":"11336"},{"type":"tags","id":"11380"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27463"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27483"},{"type":"contributions","id":"37360"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40132"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40133"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107657","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107657"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA third-year medical student is on ward rounds with the medical team. The student notices that the consultant is about to prescribe penicillin for a patient whose electronic medical record clearly documents a severe penicillin allergy.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial action for the medical student to take?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Document the error in the medical record","Report the incident to hospital administration","Draw this to the attention of the team","Amend the medication chart to a guideline-based alternative antibiotic","Privately raise the concern with their clinical supervisor"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate action is to \u003Cstrong\u003Edraw this to the attention of the team\u003C/strong\u003E. This approach ensures patient safety through timely intervention.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDocument the error in the medical record\u003C/strong\u003E - While documentation is important for adverse events and near misses, this action alone does not address the immediate patient safety risk and delays appropriate intervention\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReport the incident to hospital administration\u003C/strong\u003E - This escalation is inappropriate without first attempting to address the issue through immediate clinical supervisors\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAmend the medication chart to a guideline-based alternative antibiotic\u003C/strong\u003E - Medical students do not have prescribing rights and making unauthorised changes to medication charts is inappropriate and potentially dangerous\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrivately raise the concern with their clinical supervisor\u003C/strong\u003E - While appropriate in many situations, this may result in unacceptable delay when immediate patient safety is at risk\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMedical students have a professional obligation to speak up about patient safety concerns. The appropriate pathway is to raise concerns respectfully through immediate clinical team members who can address the issue promptly.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhen faced with patient safety concerns, medical students can use the PACE approach:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Col\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProbe\u003C/strong\u003E - \u0022Do you know that this patient has a documented penicillin allergy?\u0022\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAlert\u003C/strong\u003E - \u0022Can we re-assess the situation? The patient has a severe penicillin allergy documented\u0022\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChallenge\u003C/strong\u003E - \u0022Please stop what you are doing while we check - this patient is allergic to penicillin\u0022\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEmergency\u003C/strong\u003E - \u0022STOP what you are doing! This patient has a severe penicillin allergy\u0022\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ol\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis graduated approach allows students to escalate their concerns appropriately while maintaining professional relationships and ensuring patient safety.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Patient safety concerns should be raised immediately through appropriate channels to prevent harm.","Medical students have a professional obligation to speak up about safety issues while maintaining respect for the healthcare team.","The clinical supervisor or registrar is the appropriate first point of contact for medical students to raise concerns."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx.","AMSA Code of Ethics. In Australian medical student association [online]. Available at: https://amsa.org.au/advocacy-and-policy/","Nickson C. Speaking up. Life in the Fast Lane [Internet]. 2020 Nov 3. Available at: https://litfl.com/speaking-up/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90089"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18937"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90089","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/90089"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-01T20:28:49+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-01T20:30:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11671"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107657"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/17"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude07","name":"Bioethics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"76","links